Malabar Cements Ltd. is seeking to
buy 12,000 metric tons of thermal coal, according to a document
on its  website .  The state-owned cement maker based in Kerala is seeking
coal with 5,500 kilocalories per kilogram on an air-dried basis,
12 percent maximum total moisture, 23 percent maximum ash and 1
percent maximum sulfur to be delivered at the port of Cochin,
according to the tender  document . Bids will be opened Sept. 5.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dinakar Sethuraman in  Singapore  at 
 dinakar@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alexander Kwiatkowski at 
 akwiatkowsk2@bloomberg.net . 